  <name>uGet</name>
  <summary>Download manager using GTK+ and libcurl</summary>
  <description>
    <p>uGet is a lightweight yet powerful Open Source download manager for GNU/Linux developed with GTK+.</p>
    <p>Some highlights of uGet:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>multi-connection downloads</li>
      <li>browser integration</li>
      <li>download YouTube videos</li>
      <li>clipboard monitor</li>
      <li>batch downloads</li>
      <li>downloads queue</li>
      <li>advanced download categories</li>
      <li>translated into multiple languages</li>
      <li>pause/resume downloads</li>
      <li>scheduler</li>
      <li>after completion actions</li>
      <li>multiple mirrors/sources</li>
      <li>multiple protocols</li>
      <li>command-line / terminal</li>
      <li>quiet mode</li>
      <li>keyboard shortcuts</li>
      <li>download history</li>
      <li>FTP login and anonymous FTP</li>
      <li>folder auto-creation</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <developer_name>uGet Team</developer_name>
